Note :
check  ssh server is installed or not:
if not installed, install it (this has to be dones on server side)
    $sudo apt install ssh-server :
also check the client side if the ssh client is installed! if Not installed, install as follow:
  $sudo apt install ssh-client
After installation of ssh-server , CHECK ssh server status if running or not:
  $ ssh service status
  if you see does not work , restart i
  $ sudo service ssh restart

ssh -Y' Enables trusted X11 forwarding. Trusted X11 forwardings are not subjected to the X11 SECURITY extension controls.
to enable  X11 forwarding:
 $vi cat /etc/ssh/sshd_config 
    change X11Forwarding no to X11Forwarding yes 
$ ssh -Y root@192.168.12.64

